# Per ADR-021 Phase B (amended by issue #848): release-time `towncrier build`
# collates `changelog.d/*.md` fragments into `CHANGELOG.md`. Day-to-day PRs
# don't edit `CHANGELOG.md` directly, so conflicts there are already rare —
# this rule covers two remaining failure modes:
#   1. The release-collation commit on `main` and a still-open feature branch
#      that landed a fragment can rebase cleanly without a manual merge.
#   2. A straggler hand-edit (e.g., a one-off correction) that races a
#      collation commit resolves to the union of both edits.
# This is a belt-and-suspenders rule, not the primary fix.
CHANGELOG.md merge=union
